    {
      "id": "1002679",
      "title": "",
      "description": "To complete track improvement work, the Greenbush, Kingston, and Fall River/New Bedford Lines will originate and terminate at Braintree during the following weekends:\r\n\u2022 April 18-19 and 25-26\r\n\u2022 May 9-10\r\n\r\nPassengers can use the Red Line for service between South Station and Braintree. Inbound Greenbush Line trains will terminate at Braintree after stopping at Weymouth Landing/East Braintree, a journey of approximately 9 minutes. Outbound Greenbush Line trains will originate at Braintree approximately 10 minutes prior to the schedule Weymouth Landing/East Braintree departure time.\r\n\r\nAffected stations:\r\nSouth Station\r\nJFK/UMass\r\nQuincy Center\r\nBraintree",
      "severity": 8,
      "route_id": "unknown"
    },
    {
      "id": "1004006",
      "title": "",
      "description": "Express buses will serve all stops between Framingham and Wellesley Hills and then run express to either Back Bay or South Station.\r\n\r\nLocal buses will serve all stops (except Wellesley Farms and Lansdowne) between Wellesley Hills and either Back Bay or South Station.\r\n\r\nThere will be timed transfers between the local and express routes at Wellesley Hills.\r\n\r\nTravel Times:\r\nRiders using the shuttles should budget ample extra travel time. For example, a rider travelling to South Station from Framingham should budget approximately 20 extra minutes if taking the express shuttles and up to 70 extra minutes if taking the local shuttles.\r\n\r\nAffected Stations and Shuttle Stop Locations:\r\nSouth Station \u2013 South Station Bus Terminal Gates 3-6\r\nBack Bay \u2013 Dartmouth St @ Back Bay Station (Pickup), Clarendon St @ Back Bay Busway (Dropoff)\r\nLansdowne \u2013 Not Served\r\nBoston Landing \u2013 Guest St @ New Balance Wy\r\nNewtonville \u2013 Washington St @ Walnut St\r\nWest Newton \u2013 Washington St @ Highland St\r\nAuburndale \u2013 Auburn St @ Melrose St\r\nWellesley Farms \u2013 Not Served\r\nWellesley Hills \u2013 Washington St @ Abbott Rd\r\nWellesley Square \u2013 Central St @ Railroad Ave\r\nNatick Center \u2013 South Ave @ Washington St\r\nWest Natick \u2013 W Central St @ West Natick Parking Lot\r\nFramingham \u2013 Waverly St @ Framingham Station\r\n",
      "severity": 8,
      "route_id": "unknown"
    },
    {
      "id": "1002019",
      "title": "",
      "description": "This is to accommodate track improvement work and the replacement of 14,000 railroad ties and is scheduled to complete mid-May, 2026.\r\n\r\nSingle-track operations will be in effect throughout this period so boarding areas may change.\r\n\r\nTemporarily Suspended Inbound Trains:\r\n\u2022\t126 (8:49am from Newburyport)\r\n\u2022\t1132 (10:53am from Beverly)\r\n\u2022\t46 (1:47pm from Rockport)\r\n\u2022\t1150 (3:23 from Beverly)\r\n\r\nTemporarily Suspended Outbound Trains:\r\n\u2022\t125 (8:35am to Newburyport)\r\n\u2022\t1129 (9:35am to Beverly)\r\n\u2022\t39 (12:05pm to Rockport)\r\n\u2022\t11:47am (2:05pm to Beverly)\r\n\r\n\r\n",
      "severity": 8,
      "route_id": "unknown"
    },
